The paper discusses the automatic construction of parallel portfolios for solving computationally hard problems, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to group problem instances, which is a subfield of AI that is closely related to deep learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper deals with parallel computing, which is a topic that falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper involves the design and optimization of algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL).
